Let's focus our attention on examples showcase. Let me share its primary purpose. It was created solely to illustrate our config + create + generate + apply
  commands. unfortunately it has drifted.
  1. examples must be isolated from the monorepo. It relies on monorepo norms. Unlike our very own smoke test, `scripts/test/smoke-create-generate.mjs`, examples still has a hard dependency on the monorepo. The reason it needs to be independent is because in future, we want to extend the `create-wpk` command with templates and this showcase should serve as that template
  2. It contains more bespoke code than needed. I understand the option to seed data or to make an actual working plugin, but we should at least ensure that we actually generate and apply before adding the extra bits
	3. To that effect, I have created this file to illustrate the target config I think we can use for generation for the showcase, but we will need to first clean up the showcase app completely (even the .generated folder is a fake)
---
